## 🎤 PART 4: Demo Script — The 3-Minute Winning Pitch

### Beat 1: The Problem (30 seconds)
> "Last year, a lawyer used ChatGPT to prepare a court filing. The AI cited 6 legal cases. None of them existed. He was sanctioned by the court.
> 
> A medical chatbot recommended combining two drugs that cause fatal interactions.
>
> 73% of enterprises are deploying LLMs without any verification layer.
>
> AI hallucinations aren't just embarrassing — they're dangerous."

### Beat 2: The Solution (20 seconds)
> "TrustLayer is a real-time AI verification engine. It decomposes LLM output into individual claims and verifies each one against multiple trusted sources — automatically, in real-time."

### Beat 3: LIVE DEMO (90 seconds) ⭐ THE MAIN EVENT

1. Open TrustLayer dashboard. Show the clean, dark UI
2. Paste a hallucination-prone LLM response (prepared in advance)
3. Click "Verify." Watch the magic:
   - Claims appear one by one
   - Shimmer animation as each is checked
   - Sources light up: ✅ Wikipedia confirmed, ❌ Wikidata contradicts
   - Heatmap turns sentences green/red in real-time
   - Trust score gauge fills: "62/100 — Proceed with caution"
4. Click a RED claim — show the evidence panel with contradicting sources
5. Click "Generate Trust Certificate" — show the downloadable PDF

### Beat 4: Why It's Different (20 seconds)
> "Three things no one else does:
> 1. **Decomposes** claims by type — knows fact from opinion
> 2. **Triangulates** across 3+ independent sources — like a real newsroom
> 3. Works in **real-time** — not after the fact, but as the AI generates"

### Beat 5: Vision (15 seconds)
> "Today it's a dashboard. Tomorrow it's an API between every LLM and every user. The trust layer AI needs to go mainstream. The layer the EU AI Act requires."

